description: From Middle English unhelpen, equivalent to un- +‎ help.

verbs.description: unhelp (third-person singular simple present unhelps, present participle unhelping, simple past unholp or unhelped, past participle unholpen or unhelped)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To undo or impede the help of.
examples: When I was a child, I remember my mom busily preparing for a dinner party, saying, "If you are not going to help me, then at least don't unhelp me."

description: From Middle English unhelpe, equivalent to un- +‎ help.
